  "doc_id": "23316",
  "text": "Recently, a gate level body biasing technique was proposed [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] to overcome the speed and energy limits of DTMOS logic gates. Exploiting this solution, the RC delay in charging the body of the devices does not affect the speed of logic gates. Additionally, when input signals switch without changing the logic gate status, the body capacitances are no more uselessly charged/discharged.",
